<paragraph blockId="43.[264,1323,284,1230]" box="[312,1044,1004,1030]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
Distribution. The species is known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[892,942,1004,1030]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[264,1323,284,1230]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
Etymology. 
<emphasis box="[457,525,1044,1069]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Lulua</emphasis>
, a noun in apposition, refers to the indigenous people who live in the region near the Lulua 
<collectingRegion box="[565,632,1084,1110]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">River</collectingRegion>
, between the 
<collectingRegion box="[791,858,1084,1110]" country="Republic of the Congo" name="Kasai-Oriental" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Kasai</collectingRegion>
and Sankuru rivers.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[264,1323,284,1230]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
Remarks. A long flagellum, dense tomentum of the mesonotum, and the red pleuron below the halter, the red coxae, trochanters, and femora, and the combined characters of the terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[442,607,1204,1230]" captionStart="FIGURES 160­164" captionStartId="83.[264,382,1818,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-41@83.[211,1363,288,1440]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="FIGURES 160­164. Male terminalia of Ommatius lulua, sp. n. 160­162. Lateral, dorsal and ventral views; 163. Gonostylus; 164. Aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5080305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5080305/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Figs. 160­164</figureCitation>
) characterize 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Marascia" authorityYear="2003" box="[772,868,1204,1229]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lulua">
<emphasis box="[772,868,1204,1229]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">O. lulua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
